CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 18, 1961, pg. A14 reads: "Kappa Karnival Guests got a real bang out of the party held at the Anchorage, last Friday night...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seventeen men of Kappa Alpha Psi fraternity: from left, front row: unknown, Gregory Pitts, Howard Thomas, Ralph Barnett, Alan James, Andrew Turner, and Dr. Leon Ford; second row, : Robert Jinks, unknown, Langston Lewis, unknown, Moses Edwards, John W. Smith, Lorenzo Hill, George Charlton, Howard Hailstork, and Bob Mungin, gathered in interior with light colored curtain in background and square table and chairs in foreground
